headline.main: ALLIES' NERVE WAR AFFECTS THEM TOO; Cyprus Exemplifies Tension of Those Who Wait to Launch an Invasion

lead_paragraph: NICOSIA, Cyprus, June 30 -- Enemy reconnaissance aircraft fly over this island now and again, usually at a great height, just as they fly over many other localities in the Mediterranean theatre to find out what we are up to, what our plans are, what particular base, if any, we favor for forthcoming operations.
abstract: Cyprus: possible use as invasion springboard cited; Axis '41 and '42 threat discussed
